verbose_text: In patients with a history of congestive HF, mean baseline levels of hs-CRP, D-dimer, and hs-IL-6 were significantly higher than in patients with no history of congestive HF (hs-CRP : 3.47 vs. 2.29 mg/L, p < 0.001; D-dimer : 0.41 vs. 0.32 mg/L FEU, p = 0.001; hs-IL-6 : 3.41 vs. 2.37 pg/mL, p < 0.001; XREF_FIG [hs-CRP only] and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
